jobs.job_description:
Design engaging and user-centered experiences for web, Android, and iOS platforms.
Develop and maintain scalable design systems (e.g., Material Design), ensuring consistency across all platforms.
Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including product managers, developers, and marketers, to ensure smooth implementation of designs.
Ensure that designs comply with accessibility standards
Leverage data and user feedback to iterate on designs and increase user engagement.
Build and refine design systems and standards that are easy to scale across products.
Stay adaptable and show ownership in a rapidly changing environment, driving initiatives forward.
4+ years of experience in product design, with a focus on creating systems that scale.
extracted_responsibilities: We are a FinTech startup looking for a talented Full

Stack Developer to join our team. You will be responsible for developing and maintaining web applications using JavaScript frameworks and backend technologies. Proficiency in React, Node.js, and experience with NoSQL databases like MongoDB are required. Knowledge of AWS services and DevOps practices is a plus. At least 4 years of full
stack development experience and a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or equivalent are needed.

jobs.job_description:
Oversee national supply chain operations, including demand forecasting, procurement, inventory management, logistics, and distribution.
Ensure optimal inventory levels across the country to meet demand without overstocking.
Develop and maintain relationships with suppliers and negotiate contracts to ensure cost-effective sourcing of raw materials and products.
Manage national logistics networks, including transport, warehousing, and last-mile distribution.
Monitor supply chain expenses and develop strategies to reduce costs while maintaining high service levels.
Adjust supply chain strategies based on fluctuations in consumer demand, promotions, and market conditions.
Ensure compliance with local and international regulations related to procurement, transportation, and warehousing.
Lead, mentor, and develop supply chain teams, including regional managers and staff at various locations.
Leverage automation to enhance efficiency in warehousing and logistics.

Master degree Industrial Engineering with GPA min 3.00 
Minimum experience of 8 years at managerial level in supply chain field

jobs.job_description:
A Bachelor’s Degree in related field or its equivalent.

Proven work experience of 2 to 3 years as a HR recruiter or similar role.

Co-ordinate with the department in chargers and the candidates regarding for the available schedule for the Interviews.
• Source potential candidates from various online channels (e.g. social media and professional platforms like Indeed and Linkedin)
• Screen incoming resumes and application forms
• Interview candidates (via telephonic Interview, Virtual Interview and in-person)
• Advertise job openings on company’s careers page, social media, job boards and internally
• Provide shortlists of qualified candidates to hiring managers
• Send job offer emails and answer queries about compensation and benefits
• Monitor key HR metrics, including time-to-fill, time-to-hire and source of hire
• Collaborate with managers to identify future hiring needs
• Act as a consultant to new hires and help them onboard
• Coordinate with management and concerned units regarding the recruitment of Doctors, Nurses, Technicians, Clinic Managers and other general category staff.
• Provide information and statistics to assist in the calculation of the KPIs and responsible for HR KPI’s related to the recruitment.
• Identifying the requirements of recruitment in the facility, new and replacements and recruit accordingly.
• Designing and implementing recruiting systems for the organization and developing a recruitment plan.
• Participate in the Interview panel and support in the recruitment process.
• Executing recruitment plans efficiently.
